'''Boris Dmitrievich Каrvasarsky''' ({{lang-ru|Борис Дмитриевич Карвасарский|links=no}}; born 1931) is a Russian [[psychiatrist]], a disciple of [[Vladimir Nikolayevich Myasishchev|V.&nbsp;N.&nbsp;Myasishchev]].

== Biography ==

=== Education ===
Каrvasarsky was born in [[Derazhnia]], [[Ukrainian SSR|Ukraine]], on February 3, 1931. In 1954, he graduated from Military Medical Academy. Then he completed postgraduate courses in the [[Bekhterev Psychoneurological Institute]] and was awarded the Degree of Candidate of Science in 1961. He attained his M. D. degree at the age of 37 (in 1968).

=== Scientific work ===
He has been heading the Department of Neuroses and Psychotherapy in the Bekhterev Research Institute since 1961. During the period of 1982 until 1993 he also held the chair of Child-Adolescent Psychotherapy in Leningrad Institute for Postgraduate Medical Education. In 1986, he became Head of the Republican Center for Scientific and Methodic Coordination in Psychotherapy.
