He works as [[editorial board]] member of several journals including ''[[The Bekhterev Review of Psychiatry and Medical Psychology]]'' and the ''Bulletin of Psychotherapy''.<ref>{{Ru icon}} [http://www.arcerm.spb.ru/vestnik-psihoterapii.html Vestnik psikhoterapii: Home page]</ref> He is currently President of the [[Russian Psychotherapeutic Association]].<ref>[http://www.rpa-russia.ru/base/user/2/officer РПА » КООРДИНАЦИОННЫЙ СОВЕТ РПА]</ref> He has also been chief [[psychotherapist]] of the [[Ministry of Health and Social Development of the Russian Federation]] for about 20 years.<ref>{{Ru icon}} [http://bekhterev.ru/index.php?cid=116&crt=172,15,40 Bekhterev Psychoneurological Institute: Boris Каrvasarsky]</ref>

Proceeding from V. Myasishchev's ideas and his conception of pathogenetic psychotherapy, Boris Каrvasarsky elaborated personality-oriented (reconstructive) psychotherapy. After making a special study of this psychotherapeutic approach, some research workers concluded it to be nothing but "Soviet [[psychoanalysis]]." Its proponents, however, challenge such a characterisation.<ref>{{cite journal
| author1      = Aleksandrov A. A.
| year        = 2008
| title       = Анализ патогенетической психотерапии с позиций психодинамического подхода
| trans_title  = An analysis of pathogenetic psychotherapy via psychodynamic approach
| journal      = Vestnik psikhoterapii (The Bulletin of Psychotherapy)
| pages        = 23–33
| location     = Saint Petersburg
| publisher    = International Institute of Human Potential Abilities
| language     = Russian
| url          = http://www.arcerm.spb.ru/doc/Vestnik_psixoterapii31
}}</ref> When treating [[neuroses]], associates of the Bekhterev Psychoneurological Institute mainly make use of personality-oriented (reconstructive) psychotherapy. The method has not been extensively used in other regions of today's Russia, but has been shown capable of yielding satisfactory results in patients with different mental disorders related to borderline psychiatry.

==Awards==
Boris Каrvasarsky has been the recipient of numerous awards including the [[Order of the Badge of Honour]] and the title of [[Honoured Scientist of the Russian Federation]] ([[:ru:Заслуженный деятель науки Российской Федерации|ru]]).

== Publications ==
He has published over 200 scientific works, among them books ''Psychotherapy'' (Leningrad, 1985) and ''Neuroses: Textbook for Doctors'' ([[Moscow]], 1980, 2nd ed., 1990).
